From 74a94206a156dab51ecf5e9a6b0d563984863fe0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 19:47:30 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix mobile responsiveness on newest tour pages and booking
 cards

- Ayvalik, Gokceada and Sarimsakli tour pages used hand-rolled CSS
  grids with no responsive breakpoints, causing the hero booking card
  and multi-column sections to stay side-by-side and squeeze/overflow
  on phones. Added a mobile media query that stacks these to a single
  column and resizes the photo gallery grid.
- Booking price cards on hotel/tour pages used a fixed min-width that
  could overflow on narrow (~320px) phones; now only enforced from the
  sm breakpoint up.
- Fixed a topbar overflow on the energy-tourism-offer planning page by
  hiding the breadcrumb trail and action buttons on small screens.
- Added an overflow-x safety net to the two consulting tools.
---
 consulting/energy-tourism-offer.html |  4 ++++
 consulting/pnl-calculator.html       |  2 ++
 hotels/hotel-armira.html             |  2 +-
 hotels/hut-zdravets.html             |  2 +-
